A man has been arrested in connection with the alleged sexual assault of a 29-year-old woman in Clarkston, East Renfrewshire. Man arrested after alleged sex attack on woman in Clarkston A man has been arrested in connection with the alleged sexual assault of a 29-year-old woman in Clarkston, East Renfrewshire.
The incident happened between 22:30 and 23:00 in Bull Road, near Church Road, on Saturday 18 October.
Police Scotland said a 47-year-old man had been arrested and was detained in custody.
He is expected to appear at Paisley Sheriff Court on Monday.
 